         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">2/12/68 ¶  ¶ In a letter, dear Dr Hooker, just received from Prof. Lindberg, M.D., Helsingfors, ¶  he says that he has in the University Library there neither the Flora Novo-Zeel. nor the Flora Tasman...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">68.12.02</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1858-70, f. 355.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotation: 'Ansd [1]9 [Jny]'. Letter not found.</p>
               </note>2/12/68</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In a letter, dear Dr Hooker, just received from Prof. Lindberg, M.D., Helsingfors,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found.</p>
               </note> he says that he has in the University Library there neither the Flora Novo-Zeel. nor the Flora Tasmanica.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>J. Hooker (1853-5); J. Hooker (1860).</p>
               </note> Evidently these Russian Institutions<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Finland was at the time part of the Russian Empire.</p>
               </note> are very inadequately endowed. Without wishing to be immodest it occurs to me to ask you, whether you perhaps happen to possess proofsheets of the bryologic portions of these valuable works of yours. If so perhaps you would perhaps with your usual generosity spare them for the Professor, who evidently is a keen observer &amp; a sedulous and conscientious worker, who deserves <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">any</hi>
               </seg> support in his bryologic studies. Dr Regel would of course see anything forwarded to him. I think it is well that Dr Lindberg looks over my mosses, which I sent him on loan, in order that his views may be contrasted with those of Hampe &amp; C. Mueller, who worked on the majority of these plants before. A choice of the opinions thereon can then be taken for the cryptogamic volume of the Australian Flora.<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>No cryptogamic volume of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Flora australiensis</seg> was ever published.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">With grateful regards your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">I quote a sentence from the Professors letter which is quite touching:</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>"<seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">I will do my best</hi>
               </seg>, but beg only that you may have forbearance with the poor isolated Lindberg, who never has been rich enough for a travel to England, this in every respect richest land of the world."</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Prof Hegelmayer<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Hegelmaier. Letter not found.</p>
               </note> writes from Tuebingen, that he never yet saw flowering (much less fruiting) specimens of <name key="Lemna%20polyrrhyza">Lemna polyrrhyza</name>! Have you none at Kew? If so perhaps you would spare the Professor one.<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>No evidence has been found in the Kew archives that Hooker sent specimens to Hegelmaier.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dr. J.D. Hooker FRS</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Kew</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Lemna%20polyrrhyza">Lemna polyrrhyza</name>
            </p>
         </div>
